50|$|Propane is {{a popular}} choice for {{barbecues}} and portable stoves because the low boiling point of -42 C makes it vaporize {{as soon as it}} is released from its pressurized container. Therefore, no carburetor or other vaporizing device is required; a simple metering nozzle suffices. Propane powers some locomotives, buses, forklifts, taxis, outboard boat motors, and ice resurfacing machines and is used for heat and cooking in recreational vehicles and campers. Since it can be transported easily, it {{is a popular}} fuel for <b>home</b> <b>heat</b> and backup electrical generation in sparsely populated areas that do not have natural gas pipelines.|$|R
